<H1>&nbsp;</H1>
<H1><FONT color=mediumblue>Conventional Search and Indexing </FONT></H1>
</CENTER>

<UL><UL><UL><UL><UL><UL><UL>
       <LI><FONT size=5>Regular keyword searches approach a statement in transcripts
	 with a kind of accountant mentality.</FONT></LI>
       <BR><BR>
       <LI><FONT size=5>Logical search result yes or no with no middle ground.</FONT></LI>
       <BR><BR>
       <LI><FONT size=5>No interdependence of any kind between statements and content words.</FONT></LI>
       <BR><BR>
       <LI><FONT size=5>Lack of precision. On ave 50% of searched information is irrelevant.</FONT></LI>
       <BR><BR>
       <LI><FONT size=5>A query about <FONT color=red>“Chronobot”</FONT> will fail to find statements about 
	   <FONT color=red> “time-machine”, “virtual-classroom”,”DrChang”, ”Nocture”</FONT> </FONT></LI>
</UL></UL></UL></UL></UL></UL></UL>

